  "invariants": {
    "sendIntentExactSnapshot": "Every proof_version-2 send intent is bound, atomically at confirm time, to an immutable draft_versions snapshot (draft_version_id, ON DELETE RESTRICT) of the exact content the user approved; legacy proof_version-1 intents (NULL draft_version_id) are non-sendable fail-closed (transport.get_send_snapshot raises P0002). The worker reads confirmed content only through the private snapshot functions — draft_versions has no worker table grant.",
    "mimeArtifactImmutability": "transport.send_mime_artifacts rows are insert-verified (sha256(raw_mime) = mime_sha256, exact size, attempt/intent/workspace/message_id chain match) and immutable except the single retention-clearing transition (raw_mime -> NULL + cleared_at stamped, all metadata byte-identical).",
    "mimeArtifactRetention": "Raw MIME bytes may be cleared only after the attempt is completed/failed_before_delivery/cancelled; mime_sha256, size_bytes and message_id survive clearing as the durable proof; payloads are bounded by rawMimeMaxBytes (25 MiB) and never reachable by browser roles."
